\sin x + \sin y = a
\cos x+\cos y=b
\tan \frac{x+y}{2}
x=a+b
y=a-b
a=\frac{x+y}{2}
b=\frac{x-y}{2}
\sin(a+b)=\sin a\cos b+\cos a\sin b,
\sin(a-b)=\sin a\cos b-\cos a\sin b.
\sin(a+b)+\sin(a-b)=2\sin a \cos b.
\sin x+\sin y=2\sin\left(\frac{x+y}{2}\right)\cos\left(\frac{x-y}{2}\right).\tag{1}
\cos x+\cos y
